The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 November is 108,672 (12,525.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 November, there were 5,128 new confirmed cases (591.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 November, there were 4,490 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 14% (638 extra cases).
